To be honest, I wasn’t sure about Cinderella Phenomenon at first, because, you know, it’s free. What can you expect from a free otome game, when some 0 lvl mobile adaptations, that impossible to play [strike]and melt your brain[/strike], cost $30?

But don’t let this freeness turn you off: reviews don’t lie. CP is a really good VN and it surpassed all my expectations:
[list]
[*] 5 story rich and absolutely different routes with looot’s of choices – check;
[*] strong, interesting and clever MC – check;
[*] incredible character development of MC and guys – check;
[*] natural relationship progress – check;
[*] great story, worlbuilding and atmosphere – check;
[*] cool writing, lovely art, beautiful menu screen, cute visual effects – check;
[*] and even some mysteries and unexpected plot twists!
[/list]
In total: such a sweet game, too sweet to be free! I would give it a solid B, even if we had to pay for it. Karma and Waltz routes really surprised me! Twinkle-twinkle, little star ~
